# Implementation Plan: Fix Chat History Persistence

The goal is to move chat history storage from `localStorage` to a server-side JSON file (`chat_history.json`) to ensure reliability and persistence across browser sessions.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This change requires the backend server ([server.js](file:///c:/Users/shoaib/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/gemini-devtool-suite/server.js)) to be running. If it's not running, the frontend will fallback to `localStorage` (or show an error if not handled).

## Proposed Changes

### Backend

#### [MODIFY] [server.js](file:///C:/Users/shoaib/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/gemini-devtool-suite/server.js)
- Add a GET `/api/history` endpoint to read `chat_history.json`.
- Add a POST `/api/history` endpoint to save the chat history to `chat_history.json`.

---

### Frontend

#### [MODIFY] [ChatInterface.tsx](file:///C:/Users/shoaib/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/gemini-devtool-suite/components/ChatInterface.tsx)
- Add a `useEffect` to fetch chat history from the server on component mount.
- Update the existing `useEffect` (that currently saves to `localStorage`) to also send a POST request to `/api/history`.
- Implement a fallback to `localStorage` in case the server is unreachable.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Create a scratch script `test_history_api.js` to verify the new endpoints in [server.js](file:///c:/Users/shoaib/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/gemini-devtool-suite/server.js).
- Run the script using `node test_history_api.js`.

### Manual Verification
1. Start the server: `node server.js`.
2. Open the Gemini DevTool Suite in the browser.
3. Send a few messages.
4. Refresh the page and verify that the messages are still there.
5. Close the browser tab and re-open it to ensure persistence.
6. Check if `chat_history.json` is created in the root directory.
